# Folder Structure

Use this rule to decide where new code and docs should go. See `transcriptor-architecture.mdc` for dependency flow and design rules.

## Root Layout

- `apps/api-dotnet/` - .NET 8 solution and API project.
- `apps/web/` - React + TypeScript web app.
- `apps/transcriptor-worker/` - FastAPI worker with WhisperX transcription.
- `infrastructure/` - local Docker Compose stack and container files.
- `docs/` - project docs and high-level architecture notes.

## API Project

Inside `apps/api-dotnet/Transcriptor.Api/`:

- `Program.cs` - host setup, DI, middleware, EF Core, and background services.
- `EndpointsConfiguration.cs` - registers feature endpoint groups and `/health`.
- `Features/` - vertical slices grouped by business area.
  - `Features/{FeatureName}/Endpoint.cs` - route mapping for that feature.
  - `Features/{FeatureName}/Dtos/` - shared DTOs and mapping helpers for the feature.
  - `Features/{FeatureName}/Exceptions/` - shared feature exceptions.
  - `Features/{FeatureName}/{UseCase}/` - one use case folder with `Handler.cs`, `Dtos/`, and nested `Commands/`, `Queries/`, or `Exceptions/` only when needed.
- `Infrastructure/`
  - `Persistence/` - `ApplicationDbContext`, repositories, and EF Core migrations.
  - `Storage/` - object storage abstractions and MinIO implementation.
  - `Transcription/` - worker HTTP client and background queue/trigger services.
  - `Security/` - middleware such as internal API key checks.
  - `DI/` - marker interfaces and auto-registration helpers.
- `Domain/` - core entities and status/value concepts.
- `Common/` - shared constants and constraints.

## Web Project

Inside `apps/web/src/`:

- `api/` - HTTP client, request functions, and API DTO types.
- `hooks/` - React Query hooks and UI-facing data orchestration.
- `screens/` - page-level UI. Keep screen-specific components inside the screen folder.
- `assets/` - static UI assets.
- `App.tsx` and `main.tsx` - app composition and bootstrap.

## Worker Project

Inside `apps/transcriptor-worker/app/`:

- `main.py` - FastAPI app, endpoints, lifecycle, and job loop.
- `api_client.py` - callback client for API status updates.
- `transcription.py` and `whisper_model.py` - WhisperX execution and model lifecycle.
- `config.py` - environment settings.
- `warnings_filter.py` - runtime warning filtering.

## Placement Rules

- Put new API behavior inside a feature slice first. Do not add MVC controllers.
- Put new EF Core or repository code in `Infrastructure/Persistence/`.
- Put new migrations under `Infrastructure/Persistence/Migrations/`.
- Put web API calls in `src/api/` and consume them from `src/hooks/`.
- Put new page-level UI in `src/screens/{screen-name}/` and keep local components near that screen.
- Put worker-specific transcription logic in `apps/transcriptor-worker/app/`, not in the API.

